{"name": "hackbot", "metadata": {"name": "hackbot", "version": "0.1.14", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aiohttp", "gitpython", "loguru", "pygithub", "termcolor", "tqdm"], "summary": "CLI tool for source code analysis using the Hackbot service", "upload_time": 1732098596}, "documentation": ["# Hackbot\n\nCLI tool for source code analysis using the [GatlingX Hackbot](https://hackbot.org/) service.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install hackbot\n```\n\n## Performing a scan\nExecute the following command to perform a scan.\nVisit your dashboard at [hackbot.org](https://hackbot.org/dashboard/api-keys/) to retrieve your API key.\nEither set the API key as an environment variable `HACKBOT_API_KEY` or pass it as an argument to the command line tool.\n\n```bash\ncd your-project-directory\npython -m hackbot --api-key <api-key>\n```\n\nYou will then see various messages and results in the terminal. If `--output` is provided, the complete output will also be written to a JSON file.\nAt the end of the scan, you will get a link to the dashboard where you can view the results.\n\n\n## CLI options\nSee `python -m hackbot --help` for more information\n\n\n## Generating issues\nThis module can generate issues in a GitHub repository. To do this, you will need to provide a GitHub API key with **write issue access** to the repository you want to report the issues to (`--issues_repo`). The scan will generate an issue with the title `HB-<number>`, where `<number>` is automatically generated, and will add the discovered bugs as comments to this issue.\n\n```bash\npython -m hackbot --api-key <api-key> --issues_repo <owner>/<repo> --github_api_key <github-api-key>\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "hackbot.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "hackbot.__main__.run_main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "hackbot", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "hackbot.get_repo", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hackbot.loguru_file_formatter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "record", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hackbot.loguru_progress_formatter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "record", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hackbot.setup_loguru", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Configure and return a logger instance with task-specific session ID"]}, {"name": "hackbot.url_format", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "address", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Format the URL for the hackbot service."]}, {"name": "hackbot.process_stream", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "response", "type": {"name": "aiohttp.ClientResponse", "xref": {"fqname": "aiohttp.ClientResponse", "project": "aiohttp"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "AsyncGenerator", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AsyncGenerator", "project": "--std--"}, "params"